26/05/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Some 3,500 local monitors are to be deployed for the 3 July parliamentary elections, the Albanian Coalition for Anti-Corruption announced on Wednesday (25 May). The coalition and the US-based National Democratic Institute presented their plan to send observers to around 60 per cent of the polling stations across the country. Monitors would be present during the voting procedure as well as the ballot counting. The ODIHR is sending a separate group of observers. 
In other news, the OSCE has unveiled an initiative to promote Albanian women's active participation in public life ahead of the elections. The OSCE Presence in Tirana is hosting a forum on women and politics Thursday. (Albanian News - 26/05/05; OSCE Web site - 25/05/05)
